def plot_regrets(arr, methods=None, title=None, save_png=None):
    if methods is None:
        methods = arr.methods.fields
    data = [
        (method_names[m], ak.mean(arr.methods[m].regret))
        for m in methods
    ]
    data_x = [p[0] for p in data]
    data_y = [(1.0 - p[1]) * 100. for p in data]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, layout="constrained")
    sns.barplot(x=data_x, y=data_y, errorbar=None, hue=data_x, legend=False, ax=ax)
    # plt.xlabel('Voting method')
    plt.ylabel('Voter Satisfaction (%)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=30, ha="right")
    # plt.tight_layout()
    print(ax.containers)
    for i in range(len(data_x)):
        ax.containers[i].datavalues = np.array([55.1]) # float(f'{data_y[i]:.1f}')])
        ax.bar_label(ax.containers[i], fmt='{:.1f}')
    if title is not None:
        ax.set_title(title)
    if save_png:
        plt.savefig(save_png, transparent=True, dpi=120)

In [14]:
class CorrStats:
    def __init__(self, arr: ak.Array):
        self.arr = arr
        self.wv = arr.cov_matrix[:,0,0]  # Winner variance
        self.rv = arr.cov_matrix[:,1,1]  # Runner-up variance

        wrc = arr.cov_matrix[:,1,0]  # Winner-runner-up covariance
        # Winner-runnerup corellation coefficient
        self.wrcc = wrc / np.sqrt(self.wv * self.rv)
        # Runner-up margin of loss (number of sigmas of utility)
        self.rmarg = arr.cand_regret[:,1] * np.sqrt(len(arr)) / np.sqrt(self.wv + self.rv)

        if len(arr[0].cand_regret) > 2:
            self.tv = arr.cov_matrix[:,2,2]  # Third candidate variance
            wtc = arr.cov_matrix[:,2,0]  # Winner-third covariance
            self.wtcc = wtc / np.sqrt(self.wv * self.tv)
            self.wtmarg = arr.cand_regret[:,2] * np.sqrt(len(arr)) / np.sqrt(self.wv + self.tv)

            rtc = arr.cov_matrix[:,2,1]  # runup-third covariance
            self.rtcc = rtc / np.sqrt(self.rv * self.tv)
